1 - When should the private methods be used in a class?
ans- Private methods should be used in a particular class and methods but cannot be used outside the class. When we do not want to give the code access to the other 
     methods or class then we use private methods,it is also used to break the task into smaller parts.

2 - Do we need encapsulation for constants?
ans- Yes we can use encapsulation for constants but it is not compulsory to use encapsulation for constants.


3 What are two benefits of using the Factory methods?
ans
1-	In Factory method, it reduces the duplicacy of code.
2-	In Factory method, we can have more names to give a method name .

4- Overloading is compile time or runtime?
ans-Overloading is compile time where more than one method can have same name with different parameters.

5- What are the three ways of initializing instance variables?
Ans-:The ways are-: final methods, constructors and  initialization blocks.

6- Why "finalize" method is deprecated?
Ans-:finalize() is used to clear the memory ,but it was deprecated because sometimes it does not do the job correctly so after
that the garbage collector is introduced for collection of garbage or for clearing the memory.

7-What is the proper way of naming a package in java, show using an example.
Ans-:<domain reverse order>.<application name>.<group name>.

